OL,4,CAlexa wants children to say please
OL,5, Amazon's smart assistant Alexa can now
OL,6, be made to encourage children to say:
OL,7, "Please," and: "Thank you," when
OL,8, issuing it voice commands.
OL,10,FThe new function addresses some
OL,11,Fparents' concerns that use of the
OL,12,Ftechnology was teaching their offspring
OL,13,Fto sound officious or even rude.
OL,15,FIn addition, parents can now set time
OL,16,Flimits on when requests are responded
OL,17,Fto, and can block some services.
OL,19,FThe move has been welcomed by one of
OL,20,FAlexa's critics.
